{"id":519969897,"lang":"python3","time":"1Â year","timestamp":1625862795,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"4780 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/519969897/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"3Sum","memory":"17.5 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def threeSum(self, nums: List[int]) -> List[List[int]]:\n        \n        #didn't use dict because of sorted output\n        nums.sort()\n        res=[]\n        for i in range(len(nums)):\n            target=0-nums[i]\n            l=i+1\n            r=len(nums)-1\n            while l<r:\n                if (nums[l]+nums[r])==target:\n                    if [nums[i],nums[l],nums[r]] not in res:\n                        res.append([nums[i],nums[l],nums[r]])\n                        \n                    l+=1\n                    r-=1\n                elif (nums[l]+nums[r])<target:\n                    l+=1\n                else:\n                    r-=1\n        return res\n        \n","compare_result":"","title_slug":"3sum"}
